cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.DS

This paper deals with the well-founded semantics of disjunctive logic programs, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields of computer science. The use of argumentation and unfounded sets suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational logic (cs.CL), while the program transformations and resolution-like procedure are more closely related to logic and set theory (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The bottom-up procedure mentioned in the abstract also suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
